<h3>Mediterranean Climate with Unique Variations</h3>
<p>Napa Valley's Mediterranean climate provides the foundation for world-class winemaking, with warm, dry summers and mild, wet winters. Average growing season temperatures range from 70-85°F, with significant diurnal temperature variation—often 30-40°F between day and night—crucial for maintaining acidity and developing complex aromatics. The valley receives approximately 300 days of sunshine annually and just 25-30 inches of rainfall, concentrated between November and April. This consistent pattern allows for predictable ripening, though vintage variation does occur: cooler years like 2010 produced more structured, mineral-driven wines, while warmer vintages like 2013 yielded riper, more opulent expressions.</p>

